						               													<description>The Way Of The Barbarian (SOLO RPG)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your family has been executed in front of your eyes, your village has been burned down, and all of your friends have been massacred or enslaved. Only you survived. You have endured, suffered, trained and waited for the right moment all these years. Your sword is sharpened, the rough land has hardened you. Now is the time. Time to take revenge on those who let you experience the horror of your childhood. There will be blood, much blood, and you will not rest until the evil threat has been brought to its righteousness - by your blade.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How To Play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Never forget what you are, The rest of the world will not&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Start the game with creating your character. Roll a die on the character creation tables to determine your hero&amp;rsquo;s characteristics such as gender, name and his/her background story. After you have created your character and rolled your starting location, you begin your journey with a one-handed sword (Damage +0), three bandages, 10 supply and no armor. Step onto one of your adjacent fields to meet your first encounter. Step onto one of the adjacent fields to take your first step on your way to revenge - barbarian style.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;equip&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What do you need to play?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To enjoy the game you need three six-sided dice, a pencil, an eraser, the enclosed sheets, a piece of paper and of course your imagination. The game is designed in such a way that most likely no extra purchases are necessary. Six-sided dice can be found in almost every household, which is why the use of special dice was avoided.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Way Of The Barbarian is a solo RPG, which means you don't need a Game Master to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
